<collectionCode id="07B8AE05FFDCFFE4FCE425D62F8EF7A9" box="[1182,1204,2002,2027]" country="Denmark" name="University of Copenhagen" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" type="Herbarium">C</collectionCode>
. Ren 525
</emphasis>
, 
<collectionCode id="07B8AE05FFDCFFE4FD5525D62E55F7A9" box="[1327,1391,2002,2027]" country="China" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15606" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15606" name="South China Botanical Garden" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" type="Herbarium">IBSC</collectionCode>
) was cytologically examined. Root tips were pretreated in 0.1% colchicine at about 20° for 3 h, fixed in Carnoy 
<collectionCode id="07B8AE05FFDCFFE4FD3C25F22E75F84D" box="[1350,1359,2038,2063]" country="Romania" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14415" name="&amp;quot;Alexandru Ioan Cuza&amp;quot; University" pageId="1" pageNumber="72" type="Herbarium">I</collectionCode>
(glacial acetic acid: absolute ethanol = 1: 3) at 4° for 30 min, then they were macerated in 1: 1 mixture of 1 
<collectionCode id="07B8AE05FFDFFFE7FD5022A42E79F0FB" box="[1322,1347,160,185]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15637" name="Botanische Staatssammlung München" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" type="Herbarium">M</collectionCode>
HCl and 45% acetic acid at 37° for 45 min, and stained and squashed in Carbol fuchsin. Karyotype formula was based on measurements of metaphase chromosomes of three cells. The symbols used to describe the karyotype followed Levan 
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDFFFE7F8F223082BFAF167" box="[136,192,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
(1964).
</paragraph>
