is currently known from 
<collectingRegion id="A36DF822FFDFFFE7FCC624802E05F6DF" box="[1212,1343,1668,1693]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
(Foshan, Guangzhou, Zhaoqing, Zhuhai) in south 
<collectingCountry id="19BE7650FFDFFFE7FA2A24AC29A9F683" box="[592,659,1704,1729]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="05384B31FFDFFFE7FADB24AC2871F683" author="Wu, W. &amp; Zhou, R. C. &amp; Ni, G. N. &amp; Shen, H. &amp; Ge, X. J." box="[673,843,1704,1729]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" pagination="75 - 88" refId="ref1924" refString="Wu, W., Zhou, R. C., Ni, G. N., Shen, H. &amp; Ge, X. J. (2013) Is a new invasive herb emerging? Molecular confirmation and preliminary evaluation of natural hybridization between the invasive Sphagneticola trilobata (Asteraceae) and its native congener S. calendulacea in South China. Biological Invasions 15: 75 - 88. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10530 - 012 - 0269 - y" type="journal article" year="2013">
Wu 
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDFFFE7FAAB24AC2838F683" box="[721,770,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
; this study) (
<figureCitation id="F9922A45FFDFFFE7FBA124AC2F1AF683" box="[987,1056,1704,1729]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="3.[136,229,2043,2064]" captionTargetBox="[180,1402,1328,1999]" captionTargetId="figure-111@3.[170,1417,1302,2018]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 4. Distribution of Sphagneticola × guangdongensis (▲)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4784334" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4784334/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). It grows at riverbanks, coastlands and other moist habitats at lower elevations (
<quantity id="A6519B25FFDFFFE7FA0424C829CCF6A7" box="[638,758,1740,1765]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="16.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" unit="m" value="90.0" valueMax="160.0" valueMin="20.0">20−160 m</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="611636C0FFDFFFE7F8C724F42E26F74B" blockId="2.[136,1452,1596,2089]" box="[189,1308,1776,1801]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDFFFE7F8C724F42A79F74B" bold="true" box="[189,323,1776,1801]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Phenology:</emphasis>
—Flowering almost all year round, but in full blossom in April; fruiting plants not seen.
</paragraph>
