</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A6A94D43FFDFFFE7FCA725CC2E66F7A3" authorityName="Pruski (Pruski" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus 1759:" baseAuthorityYear="1233" box="[1245,1372,1992,2017]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphagneticola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobata">
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDFFFE7FCA725CC2E66F7A3" box="[1245,1372,1992,2017]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">S. trilobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in leaf shape (
<figureCitation id="F9922A45FFDFFFE7F8AC25E82A22F847" box="[214,280,2028,2053]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1023,1044]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,190,998]" captionTargetId="figure-13@4.[170,1417,190,998]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5. Leaf morphology in Sphagneticola × guangdongensis (B) and its two parent species, S. trilobata (A) and S. calendulacea (C). A from H. M. Li 4 (IBSC), B from Q. Yuan &amp; C. Ren 525 (IBSC), and C from Q. Yuan17." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4784336" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4784336/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). It differs from its parental species by the leaves 3-lobed and oblong (vs. often entire or sparsely serrulate, oblong to oblong-lanceolate in 
<taxonomicName id="A6A94D43FFDFFFE7F99C2A1429ADF86B" authorityName="Pruski" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[486,663,2064,2089]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphagneticola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calendulacea">
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDFFFE7F99C2A1429ADF86B" box="[486,663,2064,2089]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">S. calendulacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 3-lobed, ovate in 
<taxonomicName id="A6A94D43FFDFFFE7FBE82A142F2AF86B" authorityName="Pruski (Pruski" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus 1759:" baseAuthorityYear="1233" box="[914,1040,2064,2089]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphagneticola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobata">
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDFFFE7FBE82A142F2AF86B" box="[914,1040,2064,2089]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">S. trilobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, respectively).
</paragraph>
<caption id="35D66648FFDEFFE6F8F226372E1CF40A" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4784332" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4784332" box="[136,1318,1075,1096]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4784332/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" startId="3.[136,229,1075,1096]" targetBox="[170,1417,190,1009]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="611636C0FFDEFFE6F8F226372E1CF40A" blockId="3.[136,1318,1075,1096]" box="[136,1318,1075,1096]" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6F8F226372BC4F40A" bold="true" box="[136,254,1075,1096]" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
Mitotic metaphase chromosomes (
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6FA352637295AF40A" bold="true" box="[591,608,1075,1096]" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">A</emphasis>
) and karyotype (
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6FB7F2637282FF40A" bold="true" box="[773,789,1075,1096]" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">B</emphasis>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="A6A94D43FFDEFFE6FB47263728FCF40A" authorityName="Hoffmann" authorityYear="1900" box="[829,966,1075,1096]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphagneticola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6FB47263728FCF40A" box="[829,966,1075,1096]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Sphagneticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
× g 
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6FB9126372F41F40A" box="[1003,1147,1075,1096]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">uangdongensis</emphasis>
, both same scale.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="611636C0FFDEFFE6F8C7267C2969F4BF" blockId="3.[136,1451,1144,1277]" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">
Our cytological study lends strong support for the hybridity and parental origin of 
<taxonomicName id="A6A94D43FFDEFFE6FC4C267C2FECF4D3" authorityName="Hoffmann" authorityYear="1900" box="[1078,1238,1144,1169]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphagneticola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6FC4C267C2FECF4D3" box="[1078,1238,1144,1169]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">Sphagneticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
× 
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6FC94267C2E9EF4D3" box="[1262,1444,1144,1169]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">guangdongensis</emphasis>
. The maternal parent 
<taxonomicName id="A6A94D43FFDEFFE6F91426982925F4F7" authorityName="Pruski" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[366,543,1180,1205]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphagneticola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calendulacea">
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6F91426982925F4F7" box="[366,543,1180,1205]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">S. calendulacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 2 
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6FA2526982957F4F7" box="[607,621,1180,1205]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">n</emphasis>
= 50, the paternal parent 
<taxonomicName id="A6A94D43FFDEFFE6FBF226982F3FF4F7" authorityName="Pruski (Pruski" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus 1759:" baseAuthorityYear="1233" box="[904,1029,1180,1205]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphagneticola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobata">
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6FBF226982F3FF4F7" box="[904,1029,1180,1205]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">S. trilobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 2 
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6FC3F26982F69F4F7" box="[1093,1107,1180,1205]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">n</emphasis>
= 56 (
<bibRefCitation id="05384B31FFDEFFE6FCE326982E72F4F7" author="Ren, C. &amp; Sun, J. J. &amp; Yuan, Q." box="[1177,1352,1180,1205]" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" pagination="107 - 113" refId="ref1840" refString="Ren, C., Sun, J. J. &amp; Yuan, Q. (2012) Cytology of Sphagneticola and Wollastonia, two genera in Heliantheae, Asteraceae. Journal of Tropical and Subtropical Botany 20: 107 - 113." type="journal article" year="2012">
Ren 
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6FCB426982FC5F4F7" box="[1230,1279,1180,1205]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
), and the new hybrid has 2 
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6F93026C42A62F49B" box="[330,344,1216,1241]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">n</emphasis>
= 53 (this study), indicating that 25 chromosomes in the hybrid come from 
<taxonomicName id="A6A94D43FFDEFFE6FCCE26C42E5FF49B" authorityName="Pruski" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[1204,1381,1216,1241]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphagneticola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calendulacea">
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6FCCE26C42E5FF49B" box="[1204,1381,1216,1241]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">S. calendulacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while the remaining 28 come from 
<taxonomicName id="A6A94D43FFDEFFE6F9B426E02976F4BF" authorityName="Pruski (Pruski" authorityYear="1996" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus 1759:" baseAuthorityYear="1233" box="[462,588,1252,1277]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sphagneticola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trilobata">
<emphasis id="53DDEAD2FFDEFFE6F9B426E02976F4BF" box="[462,588,1252,1277]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="74">S. trilobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
